
[1]lucid

   LU'CID, a. [L. lucidus, from luceo, to shine. See Light.]

   1. Shining; bright; resplendent; as the lucid orbs of heaven.

   2. Clear; transparent; pellucid; as a lucid stream.

   3. Bright with the radiance of intellect; not darkened or confused by
   delirium or madness; marked by the regular operations of reason; as the
   lucid intervals of a deranged man.

   4. Clear; distinct; presenting a clear view; easily understood; as a
   lucid order or arrangement.
